A vintage-style illustration of a wooden filing cabinet with multiple drawers partially pulled out at different angles, each drawer containing colorful paper folders arranged in neat rows. The drawers cascade downward like stair steps, creating a visual hierarchy. Warm sepia tones dominate with pops of muted red, blue, and green folders visible inside each drawer. The cabinet sits against a cream-colored wall with subtle aged paper texture. Soft directional lighting creates gentle shadows emphasizing the depth and layered structure. The composition captures the essence of organized hierarchical data expanding and collapsing, with an antique office aesthetic reminiscent of 1950s design sensibilities.
